<img class="aligncenter wp-image-1369242 size-full" src="https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/uuuu.png?resize=450%2C337&#038;ssl=1" alt="COVID-19 Lockdown: FETS, other payment providers commence disbursement of FG conditional cash" width="450" height="337" srcset="https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/uuuu.png?w=450&amp;ssl=1 450w, https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/uuuu.png?resize=300%2C225&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/uuuu.png?resize=58%2C43&amp;ssl=1 58w, https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/uuuu.png?resize=260%2C194&amp;ssl=1 260w, https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/uuuu.png?resize=174%2C130&amp;ssl=1 174w" sizes="(max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" data-recalc-dims="1" /> Fast-rising Nigerian Fintech mobile money company, Funds and Electronic Transfer Solutions, FETS, operators of fetswallet on Wednesday commenced the immediate disbursement of N20, 000 conditional cash transfer to the poorest and most vulnerable as directed by President Muhammadu Buhari in his address to the Nation on Sunday 29 March. Despite the partial shutdown of retail operations by deposit money banks following the President’s directive restricting movements in some states, fets’ has been able to facilitate the timely physical cash transfer to the vulnerable as organised by the Ministry of Humanitarian Affairs, Disaster Management and Social Development at the Kwali Area Council of the Federal Capital Territory, Abuja. The Minister, Sadia Umar-Farouk who was present to kick start the disbursement said: “due to the scourge of COVID-19, the Federal Government is giving out N20,000 per person.” She said further: “Because of this COVID-19, the vulnerable groups have to expand because we are aware that there are people who live on daily wage.” “We have directed immediate cash transfer to the poorest and most vulnerable households in the country,” she stated while carrying out oversight on the disbursement. Having been responsible for processing transactions valued at hundreds of billions of naira to date, fets’ has since 2011 when it was licensed by the Central Bank of Nigeria as a mobile money operator continue to lead the pack among its peers. Its platform now serves over 2 million customers for payment of bills, money transfers, airtime top-up, among others. This disbursement further proves fets’ resolve to reach a greater number of the country’s unbanked population through the deployment of its financial technology (Fintech) tools to reflect convenience, reliability, affordability and most importantly, accountability. fets’ is one of the service payment providers to the federal government. <img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1369240" src="https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/b7df977e-e276-4c58-bfad-26dfde846194.jpg?resize=473%2C1024&#038;ssl=1" alt="" width="473" height="1024" srcset="https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/b7df977e-e276-4c58-bfad-26dfde846194.jpg?w=473&amp;ssl=1 473w, https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/b7df977e-e276-4c58-bfad-26dfde846194.jpg?resize=139%2C300&amp;ssl=1 139w, https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/b7df977e-e276-4c58-bfad-26dfde846194.jpg?resize=27%2C58&amp;ssl=1 27w, https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/b7df977e-e276-4c58-bfad-26dfde846194.jpg?resize=90%2C194&amp;ssl=1 90w, https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/b7df977e-e276-4c58-bfad-26dfde846194.jpg?resize=60%2C130&amp;ssl=1 60w" sizes="(max-width: 473px) 100vw, 473px" data-recalc-dims="1" /> Vanguard Nigeria News THE federal government, Wednesday, began the disbursement of N5,000 to one million indigent Nigerians in the country. April 2, 2020 In "News" ABUJA—THE Federal Government began disbursement of N5, 000 